  "prompt": "How do you file a complain against an online shopping website in consumer court?",
  "response": "Filing a complaint against an online shopping website in a consumer court in India involves several steps. Here's a detailed guide to help you through the process:\n\n### 1. **Attempt to Resolve the Issue Directly**:\n   - **Contact the Seller/Website**: First, try to resolve the issue by contacting the seller or the customer service department of the online shopping website.\n   - **Escalate to Grievance Officer**: If the issue is not resolved, escalate it to the Grievance Officer of the website (as per the Consumer Protection Act, 2019).\n\n### 2. **Lodge a Complaint with the Consumer Forum**:\n   If the issue is not resolved, you can file a complaint with the appropriate consumer forum.\n\n   - **Identify the Appropriate Forum**:\n     - **District Forum**: For claims up to \u20b920 lakhs.\n     - **State Commission**: For claims between \u20b920 lakhs and \u20b91 crore.\n     - **National Commission**: For claims above \u20b91 crore.\n\n   - **Prepare the Complaint**:\n     - **Details of the Complaint**: Include your name, address, and contact details, along with the name and address of the online shopping website.\n     - **Description of the Issue**: Clearly describe the problem, including the date of purchase, product details, and any correspondence with the seller.\n     - **Supporting Documents**: Attach relevant documents such as the invoice, receipts, emails, and any other evidence.\n     - **Relief Sought**: Specify the relief or compensation you are seeking.\n\n   - **File the Complaint**:\n     - **Submit the Complaint**: Submit the complaint in person, by post, or online (if the forum offers an online filing option).\n     - **Pay the Fee**: Pay the applicable filing fee, which varies depending on the claim amount.\n\n### 3. **Attend the Hearings**:\n   - **Notice**: After filing the complaint, you will receive a notice regarding the hearing date.\n   - **Attend the Hearing**: Attend the hearing on the specified date and present your case.\n\n### 4. **Follow Up**:\n   - **Order**: If the consumer forum rules in your favor, it will issue an order directing the online shopping website to provide the required relief.\n   - **Compliance**: Ensure that the website complies with the order. If it does not, you can seek enforcement through the court.\n\n### 5. **Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR)**:\n   - **Mediation or Arbitration**: In some cases, the consumer forum may suggest mediation or arbitration to resolve the dispute amicably.\n\n### 6. **Appeal**:\n   - **Appeal the Decision**: If you are not satisfied with the decision, you can appeal to a higher consumer forum within 30 days of the order.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Keep Records**: Maintain all records of communication, transactions, and evidence related to the complaint.\n- **Legal Assistance**: Consider seeking legal advice or assistance, especially for complex cases.\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively file a complaint against an online shopping website in a consumer court in India.",
